{"type":"text","timestamp":1775850602683,"sessionID":"ses_2870f726cffe8NtJ6o4FHULtTR","part":{"id":"prt_d78f14de1001zaVlrh2bl1QfVK","messageID":"msg_d78f11e1c001D8qUT92n2PuKba","sessionID":"ses_2870f726cffe8NtJ6o4FHULtTR","type":"text","text":"Based on my analysis of the AR-006 archive documentation and implementation files, here is the summary:\n\n---\n\n## AR-006 Archive Summary: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n### Module Information\n- **AR ID:** AR-006\n- **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** M\n\n---\n\n### ✅ What Was Completed\n\n**1. Core Types & Interfaces (`pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/types.go`)**\n- ✅ `LifecyclePhase` enum (Pending, Creating, Running, Terminating, Terminated, Failed)\n- ✅ `DeletionMode` enum (Graceful, Force, Orphan)\n- ✅ `DeletionReason` enum (UserRequested, TTLExpired, IdleTimeout, MaxLifetimeExceeded, Failed, Cleanup)\n- ✅ Core structs: `SandboxResource`, `SandboxState`, `DeletionRequest`, `DeletionResult`\n- ✅ TTL configuration: `TTLConfig`, `TTLStatus` with calculation logic\n- ✅ `LifecycleEvent` and `EventHandler` for event-driven architecture\n- ✅ `LifecycleManager` interface definition with 9 methods\n- ✅ `ResourceDeleter` interface for K8s resource operations\n- ✅ `DeleteOptions`, `PodInfo`, `Config` with validation\n- ✅ Helper functions: `CalculateTTLStatus()`, `ExtractTTLConfigFrom*()`, `GetDeletionGracePeriod()`\n\n**2. Documentation (Complete)**\n- ✅ `plan.md` — 10-phase implementation roadmap\n- ✅ `tasks.md` — 26 detailed tasks with verification commands\n- ✅ `delta-spec.md` — 28 requirement scenarios with acceptance criteria\n- ✅ `design.md` — Architecture, data structures, state machine, API contracts\n- ✅ `tests.md` — Unit, integration, and load test specifications\n\n---\n\n### ⏸️ What Was Deferred\n\n**1. Handler Layer** (Tasks 7-10, 17-18)\n- ⏸️ `DeleteHandler` — Single sandbox deletion HTTP endpoint\n- ⏸️ `ForceDeleteHandler` — POST /terminate endpoint\n- ⏸️ `BatchDeleteHandler` — Batch deletion with filtering\n- ⏸️ `GetLifecycleStateHandler` — Query lifecycle state endpoint\n- ⏸️ Route registration in HTTP server\n- ⏸️ Handler error response tests (400, 404, 409, 500 cases)\n\n**2. Manager Layer** (Tasks 2-6)\n- ⏸️ `LifecycleManager` implementation\n- ⏸️ `ShutdownManager` — Graceful shutdown with timeout\n- ⏸️ `ResourceCleaner` — K8s CR, pod, service, ingress cleanup\n- ⏸️ State machine with transition validation\n- ⏸️ Store integration for cascading delete\n\n**3. Detector Layer** (Tasks 11-12)\n- ⏸️ `IdleDetector` — Idle timeout detection & auto-delete\n- ⏸️ `OrphanDetector` — Orphan CR and zombie record cleanup\n- ⏸️ Background worker management\n\n**4. Supporting Infrastructure**\n- ⏸️ Activity tracking (Task 14)\n- ⏸️ Lifecycle-specific error types (Task 15)\n- ⏸️ Retry logic with exponential backoff (Task 16)\n- ⏸️ Worker lifecycle management (Task 13)\n\n**5. Testing** (Tasks 19-26)\n- ⏸️ Unit tests for all components (target: 80%+ coverage)\n- ⏸️ Integration tests (graceful delete, force delete, idle auto-delete, orphan cleanup, batch delete)\n- ⏸️ Load tests (concurrent deletes, batch performance)\n- ⏸️ Final compilation & documentation review\n\n---\n\n### Summary Stats\n\n| Category | Planned | Completed | Status |\n|----------|---------|-----------|--------|\n| Documentation Files | 5 | 5 | ✅ 100% |\n| Core Types | 15+ types | 15+ types | ✅ 100% |\n| HTTP Handlers | 4 handlers | 0 | ⏸️ Deferred |\n| Manager Components | 4 components | 0 | ⏸️ Deferred |\n| Background Workers | 2 detectors | 0 | ⏸️ Deferred |\n| Tests | 26 tasks | 0 | ⏸️ Deferred |\n\n**Conclusion:** AR-006 completed the **type definitions and specification documentation** but deferred the **actual implementation** of handlers, managers, detectors, and tests. The foundation is ready for implementation to begin.","time":{"start":1775850602679,"end":1775850602679}}}
